I used to be a member of ClubCorp and this was my home club.  I have played a lot of the golf courses while I was travelling but the closest ones  to where I live are an hour away.  When they raised the cost of the ONE program I no longer had a viable business case and they didn't have enough extras to draw me in.  I visited the Town Point club in Norfolk and that was a fine club.  The location was on the water in downtown Norfolk and they have a cigar room.  How can a DC club not have a cigar room?  Instead, they try to push people toward Shelley's Back Room which is an okay establishment but if you are paying top dollar for a private club, why would I want to go to a place anyone can go and fight the crowds?
